Check out the [Ref][1] binding in React, this allows you to access a DOM element programatically. Here&#39;s an example.

```
class MyComponent extends React.Component {

  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    this.nodeRef = React.createRef();
    this.doSomething = this.doSomething.bind(this);
  }

  doSomething() {
     const node = this.nodeRef.current;

     // Do something with the node
  }

  render() {
    return &lt;div ref={this.nodeRef} onClick={this.doSomething} /&gt;;
  }
}
```


  [1]: https://reactjs.org/docs/refs-and-the-dom.html

