The problem is that you want Link to be an _operation_ which changes the value of `succ`. In order to model change in Alloy, you need to add an ordered signature which represents the distinct states of your system. So your signature would look something like this:
 
    open util/ordering[time]
   
    sig Time {}
    sig Data {}

    sig Node {
        data: Data,
        succ: Node lone -&gt; Time
    }

But this also changes all of your predicates. You can&#39;t say that a node is isolated or terminal, you can only say that a node is isolated at time `T`.

If you have _Software Abstractions_, this is all covered in section 6.1. I&#39;m not familiar with any good guides to modeling time in Alloy outside of that book.

